{
  "query": "What are the observed outcomes of transplanting or seeding organisms onto intertidal artificial structures in Australian estuaries?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on seven replicated studies in estuaries in southeast Australia, transplanting or seeding organisms onto intertidal structures resulted in the following observed outcomes: (i) oysters transplanted onto structures supported macroalgae, mobile invertebrate, non-mobile invertebrate and fish species that were absent from on and around structures without transplanted oysters; (ii) transplanting oysters had mixed effects on overall species richness depending on the site and surface characteristics; (iii) transplanting oysters increased mobile invertebrate species richness; (iv) transplanting oysters and/or coralline algae did not increase fish species richness or abundance on and around structures; (v) transplanting oysters did not increase overall abundance of macroalgae and invertebrates; (vi) transplanting oysters had mixed effects on mobile invertebrate abundance depending on surface characteristics and site; and (vii) survival rates of transplanted invertebrates varied depending on species, site and surface characteristics.",
